Technical specifications

Dimensions & weight

Size
62.39 x 17.40 x 8.24mm

Weight
21g

Materials

Brushed stainless steel and plastic.

Box contents

1 hardware wallet, 1 USB-C to USB-A cable, 1 getting started leaflet, 3 recovery sheets, 1 keychain strap

Microcontrollers & connector

Connector
USB Type-C

Certification level
CC EAL5+

Chips
ST33K1M5

Compatibility

64-bits desktop computer (Windows 8+, macOS 10.8+, Linux) excluding ARM Processors.

Also compatible with smartphones Android 7+.

The device is not suitable for mining

Discover more user's reviews
Da L. Verified Buyer

Sept 29, 2022

LEDGER ROCKS and ROLLS

[LEDGER] rocks and I love how they roll. I purchased my first [LEDGER] Nano S+ a few months ago. I chose the Nano S+ because I did not want Bluetooth capability on my cold wallet as I was concerned about security. What I have learned through using my device, through online research, and talking with folks who use hardware/cold wallets is that [LEDGER] security is THE BEST. ✨⚡️⚡️⚡️🖤 [LEDGER] is the only hardware wallet on the market that has been independently certified by the French cyber security agency ANSSI. The devices use a secure chip element - tamper resistant against sophisticated attacks - over generic micro-controller unit chips that are less secure. The micro-chip also has an Evaluation Assurance Level (EAL) 5+ certification. [LEDGER] has its own proprietary BOLOS: block-chain open ledger operating system. Applications are isolated from one another to avoid cross-contamination (most unsavory in the culinary world, too) when using 3rd party wallets like MetaMask. When I connect my Nano S+ to Ledger Live, I am asked for a device password. This genuine check occurs every 5 minutes or so while the device is connected assuring me that the integrity of my [LEDGER] has not been compromised. Most hardware wallets do not have this authentication protocol. I appreciate that [LEDGER] provides substantial support through the Ledger website and opportunities to learn through Ledger Academy. I connect with the US support team in Portland a lot for advice and they are amazing. I minted my first NFT with [LEDGER] and BRICK. ⚡️⚡️⚡️✨ I am super stoked to be a small part of this growing global community. I love how [LEDGER] does so much that I bought the family pack bundles of both the Nano S+ and Nano X to gift those I love and care for. I will also give the Nano X a go for myself despite bluetooth because In [LEDGER] I Trust. 🖤✨

Your Privacy

When you visit any website, it may store or retrieve information on your browser, mostly in the form of cookies. This information might be about you, your preferences or your device and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to. The information does not usually directly identify you, but it can give you a more personalized web experience. Because we respect your right to privacy, you can choose not to allow some types of cookies. Click on the different category headings to find out more and change our default settings. However, blocking some types of cookies may impact your experience of the site and the services we are able to offer.
More information

Strictly Necessary Cookies

Always Active

These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be switched off in our systems. They are usually only set in response to actions made by you which amount to a request for services, such as setting your privacy preferences, logging in or filling in forms. You can set your browser to block or alert you about these cookies, but some parts of the site will not then work. These cookies do not store any personally identifiable information.

Performance Cookies

These cookies allow us to count visits and traffic sources so we can measure and improve the performance of our site. They help us to know which pages are the most and least popular and see how visitors move around the site. All information these cookies collect is aggregated and therefore anonymous. If you do not allow these cookies we will not know when you have visited our site, and will not be able to monitor its performance.

Functional Cookies

These cookies enable the website to provide enhanced functionality and personalisation. They may be set by us or by third party providers whose services we have added to our pages. If you do not allow these cookies then some or all of these services may not function properly.

Targeting Cookies

These cookies may be set through our site by our advertising partners. They may be used by those companies to build a profile of your interests and show you relevant adverts on other sites. They do not store directly personal information, but are based on uniquely identifying your browser and internet device. If you do not allow these cookies, you will experience less targeted advertising.
